# Implementation Plan - Phase 5: Admin Dashboard for Inventory Management

We will implement an administrative dashboard to manage inventory, track orders, review statistics, and manage users. This includes role-based access control (RBAC), summary APIs, reusable table views, product forms with validation, and delivery updates.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Components

We will create the administrative routes, query controllers, and summary API endpoint.

#### [NEW] [adminController.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/backend/controllers/adminController.js)
Contains administrative handlers:
- `getSummary`: Fetches statistics counts (total products, total users, total orders) and aggregates total paid revenue.
- `getOrders`: Returns all orders (populated with customer names).
- `deliverOrder`: Updates order delivery status markers in Mongoose.
- `getUsers`: Returns all user records.
- `deleteUser`: Evicts standard users from MongoDB (guards against self-deletion).

#### [NEW] [adminRoutes.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/backend/routes/adminRoutes.js)
Exposes the admin paths (wrapped entirely with `protect` and `admin` middleware):
- `GET /api/admin/summary`
- `GET /api/admin/orders`
- `PUT /api/admin/orders/:id/deliver`
- `GET /api/admin/users`
- `DELETE /api/admin/users/:id`

#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codex%20intern/Ecommerce%20website/backend/server.js)
Mount the admin routes under `/api/admin`.

